Text: My regular @ParkvilleMarket update: nice crowd tonight for bingo night! My 10 yr old and I went w J’s Crab Shack (and of course the best brussel sprouts in existence from Twisted Italian). Cathy and the 13 yr old got poke bowls from Hartford Poke Company. So good!! https://t.co/AUIczF8mzX

Just stopped by the Knights of Columbus free winter cost giveaway at St. Joseph Cathedral in Hartford to say thanks to all the volunteers. And thanks to my friend, the incomparable Mike McGarry, for the impromptu historical tour of the cathedral. https://t.co/X61C1Faqcm

My son as we were walking into Eternals tonight at Buckland Hills:

“I don’t know, Daddy. I mean, I want to sit next to you because you know a lot about Marvel movies. But you also hog the popcorn.”

The @salvationarmy helps so many people all year long, but especially during the holiday season. 

Cathy, Rider, Owen and I helped deliver meals to neighbors in need this morning. Thanks to the Hartford @salvationarmy for organizing. https://t.co/Ts62sQZ3xX

Last week, fewer people filed for unemployment than during any week since…wait for it…1969. 

This economy is on fire right now. And yes, when economies grow this big and this fast, price increases can happen. But it’s a symptom of a historically strong economy.

Thanks to @USAmbUK and the whole team at Embassy London for hosting me to talk with British officials about bipartisan congressional concern that the Northern Ireland Protocol debate will adversely affect the Belfast Good Friday Agreement. https://t.co/9Aa6OKGgu2

In London today for meetings on the Northern Ireland Protocol and other mutual security issues. Thanks to Brexit Minister David Frost, Northern Ireland Secretary Brandon Lewis and John Bew, foreign policy advisor to Prime Minister Johnson, for meeting today. https://t.co/m7mOCnv4k2
Not sure Connecticut has ever had a bigger booster than Ray. Man, are we going to miss him.  https://t.co/xzfQLotfMS
But this doesn’t line up with Republican talking points. I don’t get it. https://t.co/lM2qNIJ5V9

There is more consensus in Belfast then the headlines may suggest. 

Today I met with DUP leader @J_Donaldson_MP and Sinn Fein leader @moneillsf and both agreed that a deal on the Northern Ireland Protocol is much better than the exercise of Article 16 by Britain. https://t.co/OsubpkkgAu

Spending the day at Stormont (the Northern Ireland Assembly) meeting with political leaders. First off is Speaker Alex Maskey and Ulster Unionist Party leader Doug Beattie. 

My focus here is making sure Brexit does not upset the Good Friday Agreement. https://t.co/FEPEBr0zMo

Dinner tonight in Belfast with the Brexit Working Group, a coalition of farming and industry groups deeply worried about how Brexit - done badly - could hurt jobs in Northern Ireland.

So important London and Brussels reach an agreement on Northern Ireland Protocols ASAP. https://t.co/PjJISIzlTI

Had a great meeting today with Assistant Chief Constable Mark McEwan of the Police Service Northern Ireland to do a deep dive into the progress made on inter-community violence since the Good Friday Agreement. Thanks to the U.S. Consul General, Paul Narain, for hosting. https://t.co/CIGDUkIfEZ

Yesterday Senator Toomey and I called on Britain and the EU to make sure Brexit doesn’t harm the Good Friday Agreement.

Today I landed in Northern Ireland to learn more. Met tonight w faith leaders in East Belfast to talk about the future of north/south and east/west relations. https://t.co/5sCBmHO3N6

Today Republican Senator Pat Toomey and I sent a letter to British Prime Minister Boris Johnson expressing Congress's bipartisan concern that a failure to implement the Northern Ireland Protocols could compromise the Good Friday Agreement.
https://t.co/rIQy1XtByB

“This was open for 100 years, closed by Trump, and [reopening it] would be an important signal to the Palestinians that we are intent on being a broker for peace,” said Murphy. “Every day that that consulate remains closed makes it much harder to re-open.” https://t.co/GmoDcQuzWK

If you don’t believe our democracy in on the precipice of collapse, read this article. What is happening in Wisconsin is terrifying. 

Republicans of good will, who believe in America more than they believe in Trump, need to step up. Fast.  https://t.co/mnRq54wBZa

It’s a big bill, so I get the difficulty of summing it up in a headline. But it’s definitely not a “social safety net” bill. 

Maybe the solution is for the media not to be ashamed to call it what the President calls it - the Build Back Better Act.  https://t.co/fNmZYZKjTk
I just dropped off a turkey and some non-perishable food today at the @CTFoodshare Stuff-a-Bus Thanksgiving food drive at Hamden Plaza. Come down and help them out! https://t.co/ZEsnifoBTM
I was in Derby this morning to announce this grant. A economic shot in the arm for Derby, Shelton, and the Naugatuck Valley. https://t.co/xCRkXxJexZ

After a very late flight back from DC last night, I was glad to join Mayor @joeganim and religious leaders in Bridgeport this morning to announce over $400,000 in American Rescue Plan funds being awarded to churches throughout the city for COVID outreach work. https://t.co/MRF3ZoRjRs

What if I told you it was possible to tax billionaires/corporations A LITTLE more, so we could:

- Cap seniors’ drug cost at $2000/yr 
- Drop insulin to $35/month
- Cut the cost of ACA plans for everyone
- Add hearing benefit to Medicare

Well, that’s the #BuildBackBetterAct.

Passing legislation that help regular working people - not billionaires and corporations - apparently causes an allergic reaction amongst Republicans. 

It makes them sick when Congress is NOT just a tool to make the rich richer.

I spoke by phone this morning with Egypt's head of General Intelligence, Major General Abbas Kamel. I raised with him my continued serious concerns about human rights in Egypt, we spoke about mutual regional security issues, like Libya and Sudan.
Thanks for having me! My Keeping Students Safe Act limits the use of barbaric seclusion and physical restraints on our kids - especially students with disabilities. https://t.co/CA3KNtsOEi

There is growing bipartisan concern in Congress that Britain is going to take steps to compromise the Good Friday Agreement. Blowing up the Northern Ireland Protocols would be very bad for Britain, Northern Ireland, Ireland and U.S.-Britain relations. https://t.co/SbcdhP3Gro

Not sure a program’s expiration is “gimmickry”. Without a new law being passed, the program (and the spending) ends. And that extension, if it happened, can come with new offsets (as often occurs). https://t.co/uQt7UnVr4j

Mistakes happen. But we shouldn't have systems in place that incentive corner-cutting, bury investigations, or absolve leaders of accountability. 

The New York Times piece suggests that serious reform is needed.

It's time for Congress to perform real oversight over DoD's counter-terrorism targeting procedures. 

When we kill dozens of civilians, the blowback against the U.S. is substantial and the benefit to terrorist group recruiters is immense.

There is a mushrooming accountability problem in the Department of Defense. 

Mistakes happen in war. But when they are a result of cut corners, and innocent people die, there must be accountability, or a signal is sent that civilian deaths are acceptable. https://t.co/kEBlX6V4Ek
